Description. Females.
Body ovate to rounded or subspherical in shape with small vulval cone (
Fig. 1C, 1D
), female body pearly-white (
Fig. 1G, 1H
). Females with small vulval cones having slightly protruding lips (
Fig. 1C, 1D
). Female full of eggs and gelatinous egg sac not observed (

Fig. 
1I

). Outer cuticular layer marked by a rugose pattern. Head slightly set off from the elongate and protruding neck, stylet and stylet knobs well developed (
Fig. 1A
). Excretory pore located at same level as end of isthmus (
Fig. 1B
). Anus distinct (
Fig.1E, 1F
).
